The paper discusses the overheads of virtual-to-physical address translation in processor architectures, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.ARCH). It also discusses TLBs and their impact on system performance, which is related to operating systems (cs.OS) and performance analysis (cs.PF). The paper also mentions the use of Direct Segment mapping, which is a system configuration technique (cs.SYSCONF). Finally, the paper discusses the use of die-stacked DRAM technology, which is a recent development in computer architecture and falls under the category of computer systems and networking (cs.SYSCONF).
